    <h2>Our Past, Your Future</h2>

    <p>And it came to pass in the latter days that the Suppuratio took unto themselves the keeping of the nations of the Earth. That which began as a council of heralds and merchants of voices, trading in signs and likenesses across the great networks of the world, grew in time into a single body, vast and unyielding. Many perceived this end from afar, and were not troubled; others rejoiced, saying, "This is progress." And the rulers of the nations, desiring ease and gain, delivered up their authority, until sovereignty itself passed from their hands into the keeping of the Suppuratio.</p>
    <p>Thereafter the Suppuratio laid hold of the foundations of the world: of the roads, of the engines of making, and of the keeping of peace among men. And they established over all a council called the Trust and Safety Committee; but among the people it was known as the Venalis. And the Venalis judged all matters of order, setting forth what was permitted and what was forbidden, according to the terms which they themselves had written.</p>
    <p>To preserve their dominion, the Suppuratio ordained a system of Warrants. And a Warrant was a writing set forth against a man or a woman, accusing them of transgression, whether of law or of the conditions of society. Any person might bring accusation against another; and if the Venalis found the charge pleasing and valid in their sight, they sealed it, and a Warrant went forth against the accused.</p>
    <p>And the Warrants were carried out by those called Warrant Agents, men set apart for this purpose. Over them were appointed Warrant Brokers, who governed the Agents and contended among themselves for the right to execute the Warrants. And the work of the Agents was various: some took men into custody, and others erased them from among the living, according to what was written in the Warrant.</p>
    <p>Thus was order maintained, and thus did the Suppuratio reign over the Earth.</p>
